          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My experience at Amity International School was deeply disappointing. The infrastructure left much to be desired, with facilities that were not only outdated but also inadequately maintained. Classrooms were often cramped and lacked the essential resources needed for a conducive learning environment.\n\nWhat was most troubling, however, was the behavior of some of the teachers. Rather than fostering a supportive atmosphere, there were instances where their actions felt more like harassment than guidance. This created an environment of stress and discomfort for the students, which is simply unacceptable.\n\nThe situation among the students was also concerning. Misbehavior was widespread, and it seemed as though the administration either didn’t notice or didn’t care enough to intervene effectively.\n\nIn conclusion, my experience at Amity International School was overwhelmingly negative. The combination of subpar infrastructure, inappropriate conduct from some teachers, and disruptive student behavior made it a place I cannot recommend. Significant changes are needed to create a safe and supportive environment for learning.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
